The Biden-Harris Administration has prioritized advancing racial equity and addressing the impacts of systemic racism on Black communities. They have implemented policies and programs to create economic opportunities for Black Americans, make investments in Black communities, and ensure equitable access to education. The administration has also taken action to improve health outcomes for Black communities, appoint a historic number of Black women to the judiciary, strengthen public trust and promote public safety in the criminal justice system, protect voting rights, and reform the immigration system with a focus on racial equity.